WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:33.408 --> 00:00:35.243 position:50% align:center
Ah! My dick!

00:00:35.326 --> 00:00:37.912 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:49.174 position:50% align:center
Well. Hey, there, Shiraishi.

00:00:49.257 --> 00:00:51.051 position:50% align:center
We meet again.

00:00:51.134 --> 00:00:55.221 position:50% align:center
[SHIRAISHI]
Ah! Saichi Sugimoto!

00:00:55.305 --> 00:00:58.141 position:50% align:center
Yeah! I guess you
really are immortal, huh?

00:00:58.224 --> 00:00:59.601 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:00:59.684 --> 00:01:01.686 position:50% align:center
Wait! Where is Asirpa?!

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:04.314 position:50% align:center
Easy! She's with me!

00:01:04.397 --> 00:01:07.609 position:50% align:center
She's just up ahead,
over that way.

00:01:07.692 --> 00:01:10.320 position:50% align:center
With Kiroranke and Ogata.

00:01:10.403 --> 00:01:11.863 position:50% align:center
This is amazing.

00:01:11.946 --> 00:01:14.532 position:50% align:center
Ogata said he confirmed you were
dead up-close at the prison.

00:01:14.616 --> 00:01:17.494 position:50% align:center
That's what he told
Asirpa afterwards.

00:01:17.577 --> 00:01:19.162 position:50% align:center
'Cause he's the bastard
who shot me.

00:01:19.245 --> 00:01:20.330 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:20.413 --> 00:01:22.874 position:50% align:center
Along with her father,
right next to me.

00:01:22.957 --> 00:01:24.834 position:50% align:center
It was Ogata and Kiroranke.

00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:27.545 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Are you kidding me?

00:01:28.838 --> 00:01:30.840 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
We're going now to get her back!

00:01:30.924 --> 00:01:33.093 position:50% align:center
[SHIRAISHI]
Hold on, is that Ryu?

00:01:38.556 --> 00:01:39.808 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
How?

00:01:39.891 --> 00:01:43.103 position:50% align:center
How could I have forgotten
something so important?

00:01:43.186 --> 00:01:47.565 position:50% align:center
Aca was so insistent
that I should remember it.

00:01:47.649 --> 00:01:50.068 position:50% align:center
If it had something
to do with wolves,

00:01:50.151 --> 00:01:53.488 position:50% align:center
I should've remembered
when I was with Retar.

00:01:53.571 --> 00:01:54.739 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:01:54.823 --> 00:01:58.993 position:50% align:center
Just after he told me
that name, Aca left.

00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:00.912 position:50% align:center
And Retar did, too.

00:02:03.957 --> 00:02:06.793 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA] I was trying my
best not to think about it.

00:02:06.876 --> 00:02:09.379 position:50% align:center
So I pushed it out of my mind.

00:03:43.431 --> 00:03:46.059 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA sobs quietly]

00:03:51.272 --> 00:03:53.233 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA sniffles]

00:03:53.316 --> 00:03:55.318 position:50% align:center
Hey. Something wrong, Ogata?

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:56.778 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA gasps]

00:03:56.861 --> 00:03:59.739 position:50% align:center
[OGATA] No, it's nothing.
We do need to hurry, though.

00:03:59.823 --> 00:04:01.533 position:50% align:center
The wind is picking up.

00:04:01.616 --> 00:04:04.953 position:50% align:center
Yeah, it is.
Let's make shelter over there.

00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:09.249 position:50% align:center
We can build up the
ice to block the wind.

00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:12.377 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA] There's driftwood.
We'll use it to make a fire.

00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:13.628 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Asirpa.

00:04:13.712 --> 00:04:16.464 position:50% align:center
Come with me,
let's look for more firewood.

00:04:16.548 --> 00:04:17.799 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
Okay.

00:04:26.057 --> 00:04:28.393 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ogata,
there's some right here.

00:04:33.231 --> 00:04:35.650 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Asirpa, listen.

00:04:35.734 --> 00:04:37.861 position:50% align:center
You've just remembered
something that's very important

00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:40.530 position:50% align:center
to the search, haven't you?

00:04:40.613 --> 00:04:44.534 position:50% align:center
So... Was it the key
to solving the tattoo code?

00:04:47.662 --> 00:04:49.914 position:50% align:center
Are you really gonna
hold back on me?

00:04:49.998 --> 00:04:52.167 position:50% align:center
I'd just like some kind of
reward for all the fighting

00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.919 position:50% align:center
and risking my life
I've done up to now.

00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:58.465 position:50% align:center
Just like Shiraishi
and Sugimoto.

00:04:58.548 --> 00:05:01.926 position:50% align:center
I don't need enough money to
found a country or anything.

00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:05.680 position:50% align:center
All I want is to live a life
of luxury all by myself.

00:05:05.764 --> 00:05:09.684 position:50% align:center
I have no desire to wind up
at the center of a new war.

00:05:09.768 --> 00:05:12.812 position:50% align:center
If you just tell me how to
decipher the code right now,

00:05:12.896 --> 00:05:16.858 position:50% align:center
then you can be free from
the danger and the killing.

00:05:16.941 --> 00:05:19.069 position:50% align:center
You can go back to your kotan
and let your grandma

00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:21.529 position:50% align:center
see that you're safe.

00:05:21.613 --> 00:05:23.448 position:50% align:center
Spend the rest
of your life in freedom,

00:05:23.531 --> 00:05:26.868 position:50% align:center
hunting deer in the
mountains you love.

00:05:26.951 --> 00:05:29.371 position:50% align:center
That is what you want, isn't it?

00:05:31.373 --> 00:05:33.792 position:50% align:center
These are Sugimoto's footprints.

00:05:37.003 --> 00:05:38.088 position:50% align:center
Somebody's there!

00:05:38.171 --> 00:05:41.883 position:50% align:center
[SVETLANA whimpering]

00:05:41.966 --> 00:05:43.218 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:45.512 --> 00:05:46.971 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Hey, wait!

00:05:50.850 --> 00:05:52.894 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] I don't have time
to waste on her.

00:05:54.771 --> 00:05:57.315 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME grunts softly]

00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:02.487 position:50% align:center
[speaks Russian]

00:06:02.570 --> 00:06:05.281 position:50% align:center
[speaks Russian]

00:06:17.252 --> 00:06:19.879 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:06:23.425 --> 00:06:28.263 position:50% align:center
[SVETLANA speaks Russian]

00:06:28.346 --> 00:06:29.347 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:35.729 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:41.818 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME speaks Russian]

00:06:44.904 --> 00:06:46.114 position:50% align:center
[SVETLANA grunts]

00:07:11.806 --> 00:07:13.141 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME grunts]

00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:27.405 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI grunts]

00:07:29.824 --> 00:07:33.620 position:50% align:center
[speaks Russian]

00:07:39.918 --> 00:07:42.087 position:50% align:center
[OGATA] It'd be best
to let Kiroranke and Sofia

00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:43.546 position:50% align:center
handle the Ainu.

00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:47.342 position:50% align:center
There's no need for you
to bear that burden, too.

00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:49.469 position:50% align:center
Tell me how to break it, Asirpa.

00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:53.473 position:50% align:center
I'm wondering.

00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:57.686 position:50% align:center
Why are you asking this when
Kiroranke Nispa isn't around?

00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:02.524 position:50% align:center
[KIRORANKE]
Asirpa!

00:08:02.607 --> 00:08:04.776 position:50% align:center
Damn, how far did they go?

00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:07.445 position:50% align:center
Asirpa! Ogata!

00:08:07.529 --> 00:08:08.863 position:50% align:center
[PRISONER 35B grunts]

00:08:08.947 --> 00:08:10.073 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI grunts]

00:08:10.156 --> 00:08:12.242 position:50% align:center
--[gunshot echoing]
--[gasping]

00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.494 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Same gun shot as before!

00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:24.921 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Immortal Sugimoto?

00:08:27.716 --> 00:08:29.050 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
I knew he was still alive!

00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.635 position:50% align:center
Who is it?

00:08:32.887 --> 00:08:35.056 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
I can't see anything in this.

00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:36.266 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
Hurry!

00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:38.643 position:50% align:center
This is our only chance
to get close to him!

00:08:38.727 --> 00:08:40.854 position:50% align:center
Gotta take advantage
of the snow!

00:08:40.937 --> 00:08:42.897 position:50% align:center
Ah!

00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:44.649 position:50% align:center
Be careful, Sugimoto!

00:08:44.733 --> 00:08:47.902 position:50% align:center
The sea currents make the
ice floes seriously unstable!

00:08:47.986 --> 00:08:48.987 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:08:49.070 --> 00:08:50.363 position:50% align:center
We're floating away!

00:08:50.447 --> 00:08:52.073 position:50% align:center
What the hell are
we s'posed to do?!

00:08:52.157 --> 00:08:54.117 position:50% align:center
Okay, Shiraishi, strip naked,
jump in the water,

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:56.828 position:50% align:center
--and push it back!
--Hey, why me?! You do it!

00:08:56.911 --> 00:09:01.166 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:09:02.917 --> 00:09:04.085 position:50% align:center
[SOFIA]
Asirpa!

00:09:04.169 --> 00:09:07.881 position:50% align:center
[gasps] The others are
starting to get worried.

00:09:07.964 --> 00:09:10.759 position:50% align:center
We need to go back.

00:09:10.842 --> 00:09:12.927 position:50% align:center
[OGATA] When Sugimoto
and Nopperabo were shot

00:09:13.011 --> 00:09:17.223 position:50% align:center
back at Abashiri. Kiroranke
was giving someone a signal.

00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:19.059 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:19.142 --> 00:09:20.352 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Just come with me.

00:09:20.435 --> 00:09:21.353 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA grunts]

00:09:21.436 --> 00:09:23.688 position:50% align:center
--[TANIGAKI grunts]
--[bellows]

00:09:25.857 --> 00:09:27.275 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:09:27.359 --> 00:09:28.276 position:50% align:center
[PRISONER 35A groans]

00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:31.654 position:50% align:center
[screaming]

00:09:33.782 --> 00:09:35.241 position:50% align:center
Private Tanigaki!

00:09:35.325 --> 00:09:36.910 position:50% align:center
I'm done over here.

00:09:36.993 --> 00:09:38.578 position:50% align:center
But what about...

00:09:38.661 --> 00:09:40.538 position:50% align:center
Where are you, Tsukishima?!

00:09:40.622 --> 00:09:42.499 position:50% align:center
Tsukishima!

00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:44.793 position:50% align:center
Hurry up!

00:09:44.876 --> 00:09:45.960 position:50% align:center
I don't understand.

00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:48.338 position:50% align:center
Kiroranke Nispa
was signaling someone?

00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:49.631 position:50% align:center
But why, though?

00:09:49.714 --> 00:09:51.925 position:50% align:center
What would his purpose
be for doing that?

00:09:52.008 --> 00:09:54.094 position:50% align:center
All he was waiting for was
for you to confirm that

00:09:54.177 --> 00:09:59.474 position:50% align:center
Nopperabo was your father,
and then he ordered the kill.

00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:01.309 position:50% align:center
There's no way to know
for sure what happened

00:10:01.393 --> 00:10:02.852 position:50% align:center
between him and Wilk.

00:10:02.936 --> 00:10:04.229 position:50% align:center
But I would have to
assume that they were

00:10:04.312 --> 00:10:05.939 position:50% align:center
fighting over the gold.

00:10:06.022 --> 00:10:07.232 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA grunts]

00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:11.069 position:50% align:center
But why now?

00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:13.238 position:50% align:center
Why didn't you
tell me this until today?

00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:15.490 position:50% align:center
Because unless I'm wrong,
you've just remembered something

00:10:15.573 --> 00:10:17.409 position:50% align:center
that will help crack the code.

00:10:17.492 --> 00:10:19.828 position:50% align:center
I had come to the conclusion
that I'd need Kiroranke's help

00:10:19.911 --> 00:10:21.955 position:50% align:center
to handle that part of it,
so I just watched

00:10:22.038 --> 00:10:24.958 position:50% align:center
and kept my mouth shut.

00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:28.128 position:50% align:center
I don't care what happens
as long as I get that gold,

00:10:28.211 --> 00:10:31.089 position:50% align:center
but it's dangerous to stay
with Kiroranke any longer.

00:10:31.172 --> 00:10:34.801 position:50% align:center
He may kill you as soon as
he gets his hands on the code.

00:10:34.884 --> 00:10:38.304 position:50% align:center
Same goes for me
and Shiraishi as well.

00:10:38.388 --> 00:10:40.849 position:50% align:center
Kiroranke Nispa...

00:10:40.932 --> 00:10:42.600 position:50% align:center
Tsukishima!

00:10:42.684 --> 00:10:45.562 position:50% align:center
Ah. Who is that woman?

00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:47.939 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] The daughter of
the couple at the lighthouse.

00:10:48.023 --> 00:10:49.065 position:50% align:center
I don't care!

00:10:49.149 --> 00:10:51.443 position:50% align:center
She still isn't coming with us!

00:11:06.124 --> 00:11:07.292 position:50% align:center
[KIRORANKE grunts]

00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:09.961 position:50% align:center
[snarling]

00:11:10.045 --> 00:11:11.504 position:50% align:center
[KIRORANKE grunts]

00:11:12.839 --> 00:11:15.175 position:50% align:center
[KIRORANKE snarls]

00:11:15.258 --> 00:11:18.636 position:50% align:center
Please, Asirpa, tell me!
What is it you remembered?

00:11:23.308 --> 00:11:27.228 position:50% align:center
[OGATA] I need to learn it fast.
Or he'll catch up to me.

00:11:27.312 --> 00:11:29.606 position:50% align:center
--[KIRORANKE grunting]
--[TANIGAKI groaning]

00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:36.946 position:50% align:center
--[slice]
--[KIRORANKE grunts]

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:44.120 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:11:54.547 --> 00:11:59.010 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI] You forgot that
at Abashiri Prison.

00:11:59.094 --> 00:12:01.513 position:50% align:center
I came to give it back.

00:12:07.686 --> 00:12:11.106 position:50% align:center
[SHIRAISHI whimpers]
So cold!

00:12:11.189 --> 00:12:16.111 position:50% align:center
--Hoparata!
--Let's go!

00:12:16.194 --> 00:12:17.445 position:50% align:center
I'll be damned!

00:12:17.529 --> 00:12:19.989 position:50% align:center
Asirpa's teachings have
saved my life, once again!

00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:31.209 position:50% align:center
Tell me what you know, Asirpa.

00:12:31.292 --> 00:12:33.294 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA gasps]

00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:38.341 position:50% align:center
Sugimoto asked me
for help, you know.

00:12:38.425 --> 00:12:40.802 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Sugimoto...?

00:12:44.931 --> 00:12:46.975 position:50% align:center
[OGATA] When I got close to the
two of them after they were shot

00:12:47.058 --> 00:12:51.271 position:50% align:center
at Abashiri... he was
actually still awake.

00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:53.314 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:53.398 --> 00:12:54.774 position:50% align:center
Sugimoto...

00:12:54.858 --> 00:12:57.777 position:50% align:center
I used to have a
best friend... that...

00:13:01.197 --> 00:13:03.199 position:50% align:center
...died at Port Arthur...

00:13:05.368 --> 00:13:07.120 position:50% align:center
If you find the gold...

00:13:08.246 --> 00:13:10.707 position:50% align:center
...give his wife some...

00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:13.418 position:50% align:center
She just needs a little bit
for her to live on...

00:13:16.963 --> 00:13:21.051 position:50% align:center
And she needs surgery...
for her eyes...

00:13:24.095 --> 00:13:26.139 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
Please...

00:13:27.057 --> 00:13:29.434 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
Ogata...

00:13:29.517 --> 00:13:31.394 position:50% align:center
[OGATA grunts]

00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:34.105 position:50% align:center
You never told any of us
a word about that!

00:13:34.189 --> 00:13:36.900 position:50% align:center
You said he was dead
when you got to him!

00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:39.736 position:50% align:center
That's because some of the
last words he spoke were about

00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:43.490 position:50% align:center
some old buddy's widow
back home and not about you.

00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:47.452 position:50% align:center
Ask yourself--
Is that what you wanted to hear?

00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:49.204 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA grunts]

00:13:49.287 --> 00:13:51.664 position:50% align:center
I could never have been
friends with Sugimoto,

00:13:51.748 --> 00:13:54.501 position:50% align:center
but he did save
my life on this journey.

00:13:54.584 --> 00:13:57.170 position:50% align:center
So, for the sake of
his last request, tell me.

00:13:57.253 --> 00:13:58.380 position:50% align:center
What's the key?

00:13:58.463 --> 00:14:00.757 position:50% align:center
Did you get the name
of this widow?

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:05.553 position:50% align:center
[OGATA growls]
Yeah. I did.

00:14:05.637 --> 00:14:09.516 position:50% align:center
Tome, that's her name.

00:14:09.599 --> 00:14:11.851 position:50% align:center
That's what
I remember him saying.

00:14:11.935 --> 00:14:13.687 position:50% align:center
No last name, but,
if we ask the army,

00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:15.480 position:50% align:center
we can find records
of where he grew up,

00:14:15.563 --> 00:14:17.357 position:50% align:center
so she won't be hard to find.

00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:20.860 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA sighs]
Anything more?

00:14:20.944 --> 00:14:23.196 position:50% align:center
What else did he say?

00:14:23.279 --> 00:14:28.201 position:50% align:center
I want to... go home...

00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:30.870 position:50% align:center
That's what he said
before he died.

00:14:30.954 --> 00:14:32.872 position:50% align:center
So, for his sake, Asirpa--

00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:36.626 position:50% align:center
No, that can't have been all!
Tell me everything!

00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:40.171 position:50% align:center
Maybe about wanting to eat?

00:14:40.255 --> 00:14:41.756 position:50% align:center
Anything like that...?

00:14:41.840 --> 00:14:43.800 position:50% align:center
Oh...

00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:46.261 position:50% align:center
Right, I forgot.

00:14:46.344 --> 00:14:48.847 position:50% align:center
Yeah, he did.

00:14:48.930 --> 00:14:52.183 position:50% align:center
Monkfish stew sounds perfect.

00:14:52.267 --> 00:14:53.685 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:55.395 --> 00:14:57.564 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
Monkfish stew?

00:15:00.275 --> 00:15:03.445 position:50% align:center
Sugimoto wouldn't say that.

00:15:03.528 --> 00:15:05.405 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
Look at me, Ogata.

00:15:05.488 --> 00:15:07.657 position:50% align:center
Who are you talking about?

00:15:09.576 --> 00:15:12.120 position:50% align:center
'Cause the Sugimoto I know?

00:15:12.203 --> 00:15:15.081 position:50% align:center
He would've said
"dried persimmons."

00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:18.668 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
Let me go!

00:15:18.752 --> 00:15:21.212 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
Let me go!

00:15:24.341 --> 00:15:26.926 position:50% align:center
You need to calm down, Asirpa.

00:15:27.010 --> 00:15:29.763 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA grunts]
Just stay back!

00:15:29.846 --> 00:15:32.349 position:50% align:center
I can't trust a word
that you say!

00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:39.064 position:50% align:center
[OGATA sighs]
I guess I'm out of time.

00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:45.153 position:50% align:center
Should've known
I wouldn't be able to do it.

00:15:45.236 --> 00:15:46.780 position:50% align:center
That was foolish, huh?

00:15:46.863 --> 00:15:48.448 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA whimpers]

00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:52.494 position:50% align:center
Hey, by the way.

00:15:52.577 --> 00:15:54.537 position:50% align:center
Maybe you can help me with
something I've been wondering

00:15:54.621 --> 00:15:56.498 position:50% align:center
about for a while now.

00:15:56.581 --> 00:15:58.667 position:50% align:center
I've never forgotten the
surprising thing you did

00:15:58.750 --> 00:16:01.211 position:50% align:center
when we met.

00:16:01.294 --> 00:16:05.298 position:50% align:center
When Sugimoto tried to kill me,
you stopped him.

00:16:05.382 --> 00:16:06.549 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
Sugimoto!

00:16:06.633 --> 00:16:08.134 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO grunts]

00:16:10.053 --> 00:16:12.055 position:50% align:center
[OGATA] Even in the midst of
the battle for the gold,

00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:15.058 position:50% align:center
which was taken deadly
serious by so many others,

00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:18.269 position:50% align:center
you made a vow that day
never to kill anybody.

00:16:18.353 --> 00:16:21.064 position:50% align:center
Which always seemed strange.

00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:25.610 position:50% align:center
Didn't that father of yours ever
teach you to kill men like me?

00:16:27.529 --> 00:16:29.906 position:50% align:center
Do Ainu idols have
to be pure, too,

00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:32.909 position:50% align:center
hands untainted by human blood?

00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:34.911 position:50% align:center
What are you talking about?

00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:35.912 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Do it.

00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:38.289 position:50% align:center
Kill me. You should.

00:16:38.373 --> 00:16:42.419 position:50% align:center
Nobody in this world
is pure. Let it go.

00:16:42.502 --> 00:16:44.379 position:50% align:center
And as long as you've
got a legitimate reason

00:16:44.462 --> 00:16:48.341 position:50% align:center
that drives you to kill,
you won't even feel any guilt.

00:16:51.970 --> 00:16:54.180 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Want me to give you that reason?

00:16:56.266 --> 00:16:59.769 position:50% align:center
I'm the one who
killed your father, Asirpa.

00:16:59.853 --> 00:17:01.312 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA gasps]

00:17:03.815 --> 00:17:05.567 position:50% align:center
[OGATA]
Do it.

00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:07.777 position:50% align:center
You've got it in you, too.

00:17:07.861 --> 00:17:10.989 position:50% align:center
I know you're just
the same as me.

00:17:15.410 --> 00:17:17.620 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA whimpers]

00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:25.587 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA gasps]

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:32.886 position:50% align:center
I will not kill another.

00:17:35.096 --> 00:17:37.766 position:50% align:center
The harsh reality is, people
like you simply shouldn't

00:17:37.849 --> 00:17:39.809 position:50% align:center
exist in this world.

00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:45.273 position:50% align:center
Ogata!

00:17:45.357 --> 00:17:46.858 position:50% align:center
Ah--

00:17:46.941 --> 00:17:48.777 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:53.823 --> 00:17:56.493 position:50% align:center
[whimpers]

00:18:01.748 --> 00:18:03.833 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO gruntss]

00:18:09.673 --> 00:18:11.841 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO grunts] I will
not let you die like this!

00:18:11.925 --> 00:18:14.469 position:50% align:center
You're not gonna
make her a murderer!

00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:18.348 position:50% align:center
She will not have--the
slightest part in your death!

00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:19.849 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:18:24.521 --> 00:18:25.772 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO gasps]

00:18:26.773 --> 00:18:28.692 position:50% align:center
--Asirpa!
--[gasps]

00:18:28.775 --> 00:18:31.194 position:50% align:center
Take my hand!

00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:32.654 position:50% align:center
Sugi...

00:18:35.323 --> 00:18:37.534 position:50% align:center
Sugimoto!

00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:51.798 position:50% align:center
I knew you were still alive.

00:18:53.633 --> 00:18:57.429 position:50% align:center
'Course I am.
I'm immortal, right?

00:19:00.724 --> 00:19:01.933 position:50% align:center
[SHIRAISHI]
Come on, now.

00:19:02.017 --> 00:19:03.852 position:50% align:center
You don't want to interrupt.

00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:09.065 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
You're doing well, I see.

00:19:09.149 --> 00:19:10.775 position:50% align:center
Have you put on weight?

00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:16.197 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
Can you stand?

00:19:16.281 --> 00:19:17.949 position:50% align:center
C'mon. Let's go.

00:19:18.033 --> 00:19:19.159 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
I can't let go.

00:19:19.242 --> 00:19:20.493 position:50% align:center
Ah.

00:19:23.329 --> 00:19:25.915 position:50% align:center
But we need to follow Kiroranke.

00:19:25.999 --> 00:19:28.626 position:50% align:center
[ASIRPA]
No.

00:19:28.710 --> 00:19:31.129 position:50% align:center
